article.headline: Stony Brook 21, Brown 20
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Michael Coulter threw a 10-yard touchdown pass to Donald Porter with 47 seconds left to give Stony Brook a 21-20 victory over Brown on Saturday. Wesley Skiffington's extra point provided the winning margin for the Seawolves (1-2), who drove 73 yards in 14 plays for the final score. Coulter was 10-for-12 for 137 yards and the touchdown to Porter. Dayne Hoffman also threw for 59 yards and a score for Stony Brook. Kyle Newhall-Caballero was 29-for-45 for 267 yards and three touchdowns for Brown (0-1), the defending Ivy League champion. Newhall-Caballero threw a 20-yard touchdown pass to Matthew Sudfeld, a 23-yarder to Buddy Farnham and a 6-yarder to Alex Prestley, which gave Brown a 20-14 lead with 5:36 left in the third quarter. However, Drew Plichta missed the extra point. Farnham caught 12 passes for 121 yards.
